Note:
Elixir Translation Round-Trip Probe

End-to-end proof that the Elixir translation pipeline is REAL, not a skeleton:

    Elixir source
      -> elixir_lexer     (tokenize: defmodule/def/defp/when/case/fn/for, atoms,
                           keyword pairs, |> pipes, %{} maps, &capture)
      -> elixir_parser    (build the dict-AST: a defmodule with @moduledoc + alias
                           + a defstruct of 2 fields, two guarded def clauses + a
                           defp, a function with a 3-stage |> pipe, a case with 2
                           pattern-binding clauses, an anonymous fn with &capture,
                           a map %{a: 1, b: 2}, a for comprehension)
      -> elixir_semantic  (real scope/name analysis)
      -> elixir_to_hir    (lower the dict-AST to the hir.runa dictionary/list HIR)
      -> hir_to_elixir    (emit HIR back to valid Elixir text)
      -> re-lex / re-parse / re-semantic / re-to_hir of the emitted text
      -> structural + CONTENT equality on the key constructs

The Elixir HIR node model is hir.runa's dictionary/list literal interchange shared
by elixir_to_hir (producer) and hir_to_elixir (consumer): a dictionary is a
HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL whose entries List (16-byte [key, value] blocks) hangs at
the children slot; a list is a HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL whose elements List hangs at the
children slot; string payloads are HIR string-literal nodes read with
get_string_literal_value. This probe reads HIR fields through exactly that
contract (the decoders below mirror the producer/consumer).

DEPTH: the probe does NOT merely check that nodes exist. It asserts on the
re-parsed HIR2 that the CONTENTS survive: module member function names + count;
the guarded clause's parameter + guard presence; defstruct field keys (2);
pipe-chain stage count = 3; case clause count = 2; map key set {a, b}. A
translator that returned an empty members list (members vanish) makes this probe
FAIL.

Exit code: number of failed assertions (0 == all passed). No exit_with_code.
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/elixir/elixir_lexer.runa" as ElixirLexer
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/elixir/elixir_parser.runa" as ElixirParser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/elixir/elixir_to_hir.runa" as ElixirFrontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/elixir/hir_to_elixir.runa" as ElixirBackend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: hir.runa dict/list literal decoders (mirror the producer/consumer contract)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
An Elixir HIR dictionary is a HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL whose entries List hangs at
the children slot. Each entry is a 16-byte block: key (raw string handle) at
offset 0, value (a child HIR node or HIR string literal) at offset 8. This decoder
linear-scans those entries comparing the raw key with string_equals, returning the
stored value. It is the exact lookup hir_to_elixir's get_dictionary_value performs,
so reading HIR through it proves the produced shape is the consumed shape.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_get" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let entries be proc get_dictionary_entries from HIR with node
    If entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with entries
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let entry be proc get_at from List with entries, index
        If entry is not equal to 0:
            Let entry_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 0
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with entry_key, key
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 8
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
String fields ("_type", "name", "operator", ...) are stored as HIR string literal
nodes. This helper resolves the key then unwraps the literal to its char* payload
via get_string_literal_value, so the probe can compare tags, names, operators.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_get_string" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let value_node be proc dict_get with node, key
    If value_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_string_literal_value from HIR with value_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
An Elixir HIR list is a HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL whose backing element List hangs at the
children slot. Returning that List lets the probe iterate members / clauses /
params / stages / pairs with List.size and List.get_at.
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_elements" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_list_elements from HIR with node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Locates the first element in a HIR list whose "_type" string matches the requested
kind. A linear scan is robust to the order and count of sibling members.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_in_list" takes list_node as Integer, type_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If list_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let items be proc list_elements with list_node
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with items
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let item be proc get_at from List with items, index
        Let item_type be proc dict_get_string with item, "_type"
        If item_type is not equal to 0:
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with item_type, type_name
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return item
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Locates a function member by name within a module's members list. Distinguishes
the guarded functions from the piped function by name.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_function" takes members as Integer, want_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If members is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let items be proc list_elements with members
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with items
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let item be proc get_at from List with items, index
        Let item_type be proc dict_get_string with item, "_type"
        If item_type is not equal to 0:
            Let type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with item_type, "function"
            If type_ok is equal to 1:
                Let item_name be proc dict_get_string with item, "name"
                If item_name is not equal to 0:
                    Let name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with item_name, want_name
                    If name_ok is equal to 1:
                        Return item
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Counts the number of function members in a module's members list, so the probe can
assert the function count survives round-trip.
@End Reasoning
Process called "count_functions" takes members as Integer returns Integer:
    If members is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let items be proc list_elements with members
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc size from List with items
    Let found be 0
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let item be proc get_at from List with items, index
        Let item_type be proc dict_get_string with item, "_type"
        If item_type is not equal to 0:
            Let type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with item_type, "function"
            If type_ok is equal to 1:
                Set found to found plus 1
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return found
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the element count of a HIR list node (0 when absent). Used to assert pipe
stage count, case clause count, defstruct field count, etc.
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_count" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let items be proc list_elements with node
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc size from List with items
End Process

@Reasoning:
True (1) when a HIR list of pair nodes contains a pair whose key is an atom whose
value resolves (with the leading ':' stripped) to the target name. Used to assert
the map key set {a, b} and the defstruct field keys survive. The key may be an
atom node (":a") or an identifier node ("a").
@End Reasoning
Process called "pair_list_has_key" takes pairs_node as Integer, want_key as Integer returns Integer:
    If pairs_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let items be proc list_elements with pairs_node
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with items
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let pair be proc get_at from List with items, index
        If pair is not equal to 0:
            Let key be proc dict_get with pair, "key"
            Let key_name be proc key_simple_name with key
            If key_name is not equal to 0:
                Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with key_name, want_key
                If matches is equal to 1:
                    Return 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Extracts a simple key name from a key node. An atom key value ":a" yields "a" (the
leading colon stripped); an identifier key yields its name. Returns 0 otherwise.
@End Reasoning
Process called "key_simple_name" takes key as Integer returns Integer:
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let nt be proc dict_get_string with key, "_type"
    If nt is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let is_atom be proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "atom"
    If is_atom is equal to 1:
        Let value be proc dict_get_string with key, "value"
        If value is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with value
        If len is equal to 0:
            Return value
        End If
        Let first be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value, 0
        If first is equal to 58:
            Return proc string_substring from StringPrim with value, 1, len minus 1
        End If
        Return value
    End If

    Let is_id be proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "identifier"
    If is_id is equal to 1:
        Return proc dict_get_string with key, "name"
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pipeline helper
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Each round of the probe runs the identical front-of-pipeline (lex -> tokenize ->
parse -> semantic -> to_hir). Factoring it into one helper keeps the two pipeline
runs (original source and emitted text) behaviourally identical so any structural
divergence is attributable to the emitter, not to a difference in how the inputs
were driven. elixir_to_hir_from_source already runs lex/parse/semantic/lower as a
unit; this wrapper just guards the source.
@End Reasoning
Process called "source_to_hir" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    If source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc elixir_to_hir_from_source from ElixirFrontend with source
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Probe entry point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "Elixir translation round-trip"

    Note:
    Representative program exercising the full declaration surface:
    - defmodule Calc with @moduledoc + alias + a defstruct of 2 fields (total, items)
    - two guarded def clauses of classify/1 (when x > 0 / when x < 0) and a defp helper
    - a function pipeline/1 with a 3-stage |> pipe
    - a function categorize/1 with a case of 2 pattern-binding clauses
    - a function mapper/1 returning an anonymous fn with an &capture body
    - a function build_map/0 returning %{a: 1, b: 2}
    - a function squares/0 with a for comprehension
    :End Note
    Let source be "defmodule Calc do\n@moduledoc \"calc\"\nalias Foo.Bar\ndefstruct [total: 0, items: []]\ndef classify(x) when x > 0 do\n:positive\nend\ndef classify(x) when x < 0 do\n:negative\nend\ndefp helper(n) do\nn\nend\ndef pipeline(x) do\nx |> double() |> increment()\nend\ndef categorize(v) do\ncase v do\n{:ok, value} -> value\n{:error, reason} -> reason\nend\nend\ndef mapper(list) do\nfn item -> &process(item) end\nend\ndef build_map() do\n%{a: 1, b: 2}\nend\ndef squares() do\nfor n <- [1, 2, 3] do\nn\nend\nend\nend\n"

    Note: --- Stage 0-2: source -> HIR1 (lex, tokenize, parse, semantic, lower) ---
    Let lexer be proc create_elixir_lexer from ElixirLexer with source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "lexer created", lexer

    Let tokens be proc tokenize_elixir from ElixirLexer with lexer
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "tokenizer produced tokens", tokens

    Let parser be proc create_elixir_parser from ElixirParser with tokens
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "parser created", parser

    Let ast be proc parse_elixir_source from ElixirParser with parser
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "parser produced Elixir AST", ast

    Let hir1 be proc elixir_to_hir_from_source from ElixirFrontend with source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "frontend produced HIR module", hir1

    Note: Root must be a dict node tagged "elixir_module" with members.
    Let mod_type be proc dict_get_string with hir1, "_type"
    Let mod_type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with mod_type, "elixir_module"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "HIR root is an elixir_module", mod_type_ok, 1

    Let mod_name be proc dict_get_string with hir1, "name"
    Let mod_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with mod_name, "Calc"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "module name is 'Calc'", mod_name_ok, 1

    Let members be proc dict_get with hir1, "members"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "module has members", members
    Let member_elems be proc list_elements with members
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "members is a list", member_elems
    Let member_count be proc size from List with member_elems
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "module has at least 9 members", member_count, 9

    Note: --- function names + count survive (depth, not just existence) ---
    Let fn_count be proc count_functions with members
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "module has at least 8 functions", fn_count, 8

    Let classify_fn be proc find_function with members, "classify"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "function 'classify' present by name", classify_fn
    Let pipeline_fn be proc find_function with members, "pipeline"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "function 'pipeline' present by name", pipeline_fn
    Let categorize_fn be proc find_function with members, "categorize"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "function 'categorize' present by name", categorize_fn
    Let helper_fn be proc find_function with members, "helper"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "private function 'helper' present by name", helper_fn

    Note: --- guarded clause: param + guard presence survive ---
    Let classify_clauses be proc dict_get with classify_fn, "clauses"
    Let classify_clause_count be proc list_count with classify_clauses
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "classify has >= 1 clause", classify_clause_count, 1
    Let classify_clause_items be proc list_elements with classify_clauses
    Let classify_clause0 be proc get_at from List with classify_clause_items, 0
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "classify clause 0 present", classify_clause0
    Let classify_params be proc dict_get with classify_clause0, "params"
    Let classify_param_count be proc list_count with classify_params
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "classify clause has >= 1 param", classify_param_count, 1
    Let classify_guard be proc dict_get with classify_clause0, "guard"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "classify clause has a guard", classify_guard

    Note: --- defstruct field keys (2) survive ---
    Let defstruct_node be proc find_in_list with members, "defstruct"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "defstruct node present", defstruct_node
    Let defstruct_fields be proc dict_get with defstruct_node, "fields"
    Let defstruct_field_count be proc list_count with defstruct_fields
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "defstruct has 2 fields", defstruct_field_count, 2
    Let has_total be proc pair_list_has_key with defstruct_fields, "total"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "defstruct has field 'total'", has_total, 1
    Let has_items be proc pair_list_has_key with defstruct_fields, "items"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "defstruct has field 'items'", has_items, 1

    Note: --- pipe-chain stage count = 3 survives ---
    Let pipe_node be proc find_pipe_in_function with pipeline_fn
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "pipe node present in pipeline/1", pipe_node
    Let pipe_stages be proc dict_get with pipe_node, "stages"
    Let pipe_stage_count be proc list_count with pipe_stages
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "pipe has 3 stages", pipe_stage_count, 3

    Note: --- case clause count = 2 survives ---
    Let case_node be proc find_case_in_function with categorize_fn
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "case node present in categorize/1", case_node
    Let case_clauses be proc dict_get with case_node, "clauses"
    Let case_clause_count be proc list_count with case_clauses
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "case has 2 clauses", case_clause_count, 2

    Note: --- map key set {a, b} survives ---
    Let build_map_fn be proc find_function with members, "build_map"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "function 'build_map' present", build_map_fn
    Let map_node be proc find_map_in_function with build_map_fn
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "map node present in build_map/0", map_node
    Let map_pairs be proc dict_get with map_node, "pairs"
    Let map_pair_count be proc list_count with map_pairs
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "map has 2 pairs", map_pair_count, 2
    Let map_has_a be proc pair_list_has_key with map_pairs, "a"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "map has key 'a'", map_has_a, 1
    Let map_has_b be proc pair_list_has_key with map_pairs, "b"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "map has key 'b'", map_has_b, 1

    Note: --- Stage 3: HIR1 -> Elixir text ---
    Let emitted be proc generate_elixir_from_hir from ElixirBackend with hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "backend produced Elixir text", emitted
    Let emitted_len be proc string_length from StringCore with emitted
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "emitted Elixir is non-empty", emitted_len, 0

    Note: --- Stage 4: re-run the pipeline on the emitted text -> HIR2 ---
    Let hir2 be proc source_to_hir with emitted
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-parse of emitted Elixir produced HIR2", hir2

    Let mod2_type be proc dict_get_string with hir2, "_type"
    Let mod2_type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with mod2_type, "elixir_module"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip root is an elixir_module", mod2_type_ok, 1

    Let mod2_name be proc dict_get_string with hir2, "name"
    Let mod2_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with mod2_name, "Calc"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves module name 'Calc'", mod2_name_ok, 1

    Let members2 be proc dict_get with hir2, "members"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip module has members", members2

    Note: --- Stage 5: CONTENT equality on the key constructs (HIR2) ---

    Note: function names + count survive round-trip
    Let fn2_count be proc count_functions with members2
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves >= 8 functions", fn2_count, 8
    Let classify2 be proc find_function with members2, "classify"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves function 'classify'", classify2
    Let pipeline2 be proc find_function with members2, "pipeline"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves function 'pipeline'", pipeline2
    Let categorize2 be proc find_function with members2, "categorize"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves function 'categorize'", categorize2
    Let helper2 be proc find_function with members2, "helper"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves private function 'helper'", helper2

    Note: guarded clause param + guard survive round-trip
    Let classify2_clauses be proc dict_get with classify2, "clauses"
    Let classify2_clause_items be proc list_elements with classify2_clauses
    Let classify2_clause0 be proc get_at from List with classify2_clause_items, 0
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip classify clause 0 present", classify2_clause0
    Let classify2_params be proc dict_get with classify2_clause0, "params"
    Let classify2_param_count be proc list_count with classify2_params
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves classify param", classify2_param_count, 1
    Let classify2_guard be proc dict_get with classify2_clause0, "guard"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves classify guard", classify2_guard

    Note: defstruct field keys survive round-trip
    Let defstruct2 be proc find_in_list with members2, "defstruct"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves defstruct node", defstruct2
    Let defstruct2_fields be proc dict_get with defstruct2, "fields"
    Let defstruct2_field_count be proc list_count with defstruct2_fields
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 2 defstruct fields", defstruct2_field_count, 2
    Let has_total2 be proc pair_list_has_key with defstruct2_fields, "total"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves defstruct field 'total'", has_total2, 1
    Let has_items2 be proc pair_list_has_key with defstruct2_fields, "items"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves defstruct field 'items'", has_items2, 1

    Note: pipe stage count survives round-trip
    Let pipe2 be proc find_pipe_in_function with pipeline2
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves pipe node", pipe2
    Let pipe2_stages be proc dict_get with pipe2, "stages"
    Let pipe2_stage_count be proc list_count with pipe2_stages
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 3 pipe stages", pipe2_stage_count, 3

    Note: case clause count survives round-trip
    Let case2 be proc find_case_in_function with categorize2
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves case node", case2
    Let case2_clauses be proc dict_get with case2, "clauses"
    Let case2_clause_count be proc list_count with case2_clauses
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 2 case clauses", case2_clause_count, 2

    Note: map key set survives round-trip
    Let build_map2 be proc find_function with members2, "build_map"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves function 'build_map'", build_map2
    Let map2 be proc find_map_in_function with build_map2
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves map node", map2
    Let map2_pairs be proc dict_get with map2, "pairs"
    Let map2_pair_count be proc list_count with map2_pairs
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 2 map pairs", map2_pair_count, 2
    Let map2_has_a be proc pair_list_has_key with map2_pairs, "a"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves map key 'a'", map2_has_a, 1
    Let map2_has_b be proc pair_list_has_key with map2_pairs, "b"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves map key 'b'", map2_has_b, 1

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results
    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    proc destroy_test_results from TestUtils with results

    Return failed
End Process

@Reasoning:
Finds the first pipe node inside a function's clause bodies. Each clause's body is
a statement list; the first statement of the pipeline function is the pipe
expression. Scans every clause body for a "pipe"-tagged node.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_pipe_in_function" takes func as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc find_tag_in_function_bodies with func, "pipe"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Finds the first case node inside a function's clause bodies.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_case_in_function" takes func as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc find_tag_in_function_bodies with func, "case"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Finds the first map node inside a function's clause bodies.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_map_in_function" takes func as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc find_tag_in_function_bodies with func, "map"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Scans every clause body statement of a function looking for a node whose "_type"
matches the requested tag. Returns the first match or 0. Bounded by clause count
and body length, so it always terminates.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_tag_in_function_bodies" takes func as Integer, tag as Integer returns Integer:
    If func is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let clauses be proc dict_get with func, "clauses"
    If clauses is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let clause_items be proc list_elements with clauses
    If clause_items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let clause_count be proc size from List with clause_items
    Let ci be 0
    While ci is less than clause_count:
        Let clause be proc get_at from List with clause_items, ci
        If clause is not equal to 0:
            Let body be proc dict_get with clause, "body"
            If body is not equal to 0:
                Let body_items be proc list_elements with body
                If body_items is not equal to 0:
                    Let body_count be proc size from List with body_items
                    Let bi be 0
                    While bi is less than body_count:
                        Let stmt be proc get_at from List with body_items, bi
                        Let stmt_type be proc dict_get_string with stmt, "_type"
                        If stmt_type is not equal to 0:
                            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with stmt_type, tag
                            If matches is equal to 1:
                                Return stmt
                            End If
                        End If
                        Set bi to bi plus 1
                    End While
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set ci to ci plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process
